$_REQUEST:

Variable is independent of the request Type or it can handle both the request GET and POST
$_REQUEST= $_GET + $_POST
           ?[n>=1] + ?[n=0]
		   
If ?n=1 get request key=1 $_GET = $_REQUEST
If ?n=0 Post request key=1 $_POST = $_REQUEST


====================
condtion 1)when ?n>=1 then generates Get request

save=7Javtask3.html
<html>
<head></head>
<body>
<form action="7Jantask4.php" method="get">
Enter Your Name:<br/>
<input type="text" name="uname"/><br/><br/>
<input type="submit" value="SUBMIT" name="btn"/>
</form>
</body>
</html>	

save=7Jantask4.php
<?php
echo "REQUEST TYPE IS ",$_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'];
echo "<br/>QUERY STRING is ",$_SERVER['QUERY_STRING'];
echo '<br/> $_GET Keys ';
print_r($_GET);
echo '<br/>$_REQUEST Keys ';
print_r($_REQUEST);

?>

Output:
REQUEST TYPE IS GET
QUERY STRING is uname=ravi&btn=SUBMIT
$_GET Keys Array ( [uname] => ravi [btn] => SUBMIT )
$_REQUEST Keys Array ( [uname] => ravi [btn] => SUBMIT )
============================================================================================
condtion 2)when ?n=1 then generates POST request

