$_POST Keys Array ( [uname] => ranjana [btn] => SUBMIT )
$_REQUEST Keys Array ( [uname] => ranjana [btn] => SUBMIT )
==================================================================================================================
How to send both request :PATCH(update single data )Request and PUT(update multiple data)request
action = "update.php?id=10"
update<tablename> set name = '$name' where id='$id';[PATCH]
                                |	            |GET
                               POST
update <tablename> set name="$name",class="$class",mobile="$mobile" where id="$id";[PUT]

How to generate PATCH request and PUT request:
we know that if we want to update the data in the database then we have to send either PUT request or 
PATCH request.
For Fully Updation=Use PUT Request
For Partially Updation=Use PATCH Request

Query For PUT Request:
---------------------------------
DATABASE SCHEMA:
---------------------------------
Table:Student
---------------------------------
 id | Name   |  Class   |  Marks|
 1  | Ravi   |  12      |  99   | 
 2  | Chavi  |  10      |  89   |
---------------------------------

update Student set marks='100' where id='1';[Its the PATCH Request]

fully update = fully changed in value of auxillary Columns set.
auxillary Columns Set=total columns - (numbers of key or composite key):
which columns is called auxillary columns where is the no primary key or composite key available.
if n<=3 Then its the PUT request

if n<3 then its the PATCH request
Here n=number of columns
===========
In Order o sent both the request use ? query String and method  is post,
? query String keyname = which is unique and will not be changed .
?id=1111

post= whose value can be changed name,class,marks.

==========================
<!-- PATCH REQUEST When request is post-->
#save=7Jantask7.php
<html>
<head>
<?php
$id=1111;
echo "<h1>Current Page Request <i>",$_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'],"</i></h1>";
?>
</head>
<body>
<h1>$_REQUEST as super Globals PUT/PATCH REQUEST</h1>
<form action="7Jantask8.php?id=<?php echo $id; ?>" method="post">
Enter Your Name:<br/>
<input type="text" name="uname"/><br/><br/>
<input type="submit" value="SUBMIT" name="btn"/>
</form>
</body>
</html>	

<?php
#save=7Jantask8.php

print_r($_REQUEST);
?>

Output:
Array ( [id] => 1111 [uname] => ranjana [btn] => SUBMIT )

